The scenario involves a combustion control system maintaining an air/fuel ratio, where both streams are assumed to be measured by differential-pressure devices. Actual volumetric flow is therefore proportional to the square root of the measured \(\Delta P\).
- Air measurement includes the square-root extraction, so the transmitted air signal \(A_\text{sig}\) is linear with true air flow.
